date: Sun Feb 06 2022 17:28:14 GMT+1100 (Australian Eastern Daylight Time)
description:
Kelly Slater has won for an eighth time at Pipeline, 30 years after his first victory at the famous surf break in Hawaii. 
 The 11-time world champion dominated the decider in the season-opening WSL event against 22-year-old Hawaiian Seth Moniz. 
 The win was Slater's first since Tahiti 2016 and capped a wild campaign on the famous North Shore break that included an incredible buzzer-beating barrel.
